729 (h) For the purposes of this section, "common ownership
730 and control" shall have the following meaning, as applicable:
731 (1) In the case of stock corporations, the direct or
732 indirect ownership of 80 percent or more of the outstanding
733 voting stock of two or more corporations by the same
734 shareholder or shareholders.
735 (2) In the case of mutual corporations, the direct or
736 indirect ownership of 80 percent or more of the surplus and
737 the voting power of two or more corporations by the same
738 member or members.
739 (i) In the case of a branch captive insurance company,
740 the tax provided for in this section shall apply only to the
741 branch business of the company.
742 (j) If a captive insurance company has been licensed
743 for less than a full calendar year and has written premiums
744 the tax for which is less than the minimum set forth in this
745 section, the tax due shall be prorated as follows:
746 (1) If licensed on or before March 31, 100 percent.
747 (2) If licensed April 1 to June 30, 75 percent.
748 (3) If licensed July 1 to September 30, 50 percent.
749 (4) If licensed October 1 to December 31, 25 percent.
750 (k) If a captive insurance company surrenders its
751 license and the calculated tax on premiums written during the
752 calendar year is less than the minimum set forth in this
753 section, the tax due shall be prorated as follows:
754 (1) If surrendered on or before March 31, 25 percent.
755 (2) If surrendered April 1 to June 30, 50 percent.
756 (3) If surrendered July 1 to September 30, 75 percent.
